# Verification Plan

## Setup
1. cd /home/user/myproject
2. npm install
3. npm start &  # Wait for server to start on port 3000

## Verification Steps
1. **Seed Database**:
   - Request: POST http://localhost:3000/seed
     Body: 
     [
       {
         "name": "TechCorp",
         "departments": [
           {
             "name": "Engineering",
             "status": "active",
             "employees": [
               {"name": "Alice", "role": "senior"},
               {"name": "Bob", "role": "junior"}
             ]
           },
           {
             "name": "Sales",
             "status": "inactive",
             "employees": [
               {"name": "Charlie", "role": "senior"}
             ]
           }
         ]
       },
       {
         "name": "EmptyCorp",
         "departments": []
       }
     ]
   - Expected: Status 200
2. **Verify Filtered Query**:
   - Request: GET http://localhost:3000/companies/filtered
   - Expected: Status 200, response is a JSON array matching the following structure exactly (order of companies may vary, but content must match):
     [
       {
         "name": "TechCorp",
         "departments": [
           {
             "name": "Engineering",
             "status": "active",
             "employees": [
               {"name": "Alice", "role": "senior"}
             ]
           }
         ]
       },
       {
         "name": "EmptyCorp",
         "departments": []
       }
     ]
     (Note: The 'Sales' department is excluded because it is inactive. 'Bob' is excluded because he is junior. 'EmptyCorp' is included despite having no active departments. 'Engineering' would be included even if it had no senior employees, though in this test it has Alice.)
